'''红屋博物馆'''（Red Lodge Museum）是[[英格兰|英格兰]][[布里斯托尔|布里斯托尔]]的一座历史建筑博物馆。这栋建筑属于[[都铎时代建筑|都铎]]/[[伊丽莎白时代建筑|伊丽莎白时代]]风格，建于1579-1580年，<ref name=" Bristol Council Red Lodge Museum ">{{cite web|year=2012 |url=http://www.bristol.gov.uk/page/leisure-and-culture/red-lodge-museum |title=Red Lodge Museum |publisher=Bristol City Council |accessdate=16 September 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929113311/http://www.bristol.gov.uk/page/leisure-and-culture/red-lodge-museum |archivedate=29 September 2013 }}</ref> 可能是由[[塞巴斯蒂亚诺·塞利奥|塞巴斯蒂亚诺·塞利奥]]设计。<ref name="Leech">The Town House in Medieval and Early Modern Bristol, English Heritage, 2014.</ref>。后来在乔治王时代进行了扩建，在1730年左右进行了改建，在20世纪初期进行了重建，最终形成了现今的模样。如今，这栋建筑已经被列为英格兰一级登录建筑。

红屋是一个免费的博物馆，靠捐赠维持运营，由布里斯托尔市议会管理。

博物馆的开放时间为4月1日至12月31日的周六、周日、周一和周二，上午11点至下午4点。

==历史==
[[Image:The_Red_Lodge_Museum_Garden_-_Bristol.jpg|thumb]]
红屋的主人约翰·杨爵士出身商人家庭，是[[亨利八世|亨利八世]]和[[伊丽莎白一世|伊丽莎白一世]]的朝臣<ref name="A Bristol Miscellany">{{cite book | year = 1985 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=bYBnAAAAMAAJ&q=john+young+bristol+courtier&pg=PA6 | title = A Bristol Miscellany| publisher = Alan Sutton Publishing Limited | accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Maclean |first1=John |title=The Family of Yonge, or Young, of Bristol, and on the Red Lodge |journal=Transactions of the Bristol and Gloucestershire Archaeological Society |date=1890 |volume=15 |pages=227–245 |url=http://www2.glos.ac.uk/bgas/tbgas/v015/bg015227.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305014355/http://www2.glos.ac.uk/bgas/tbgas/v015/bg015227.pdf |archivedate= 5 March 2016 }}</ref>  <ref name=" Feuding Gentry ">{{cite web|year=2004 |url=http://www2.glos.ac.uk/bgas/tbgas/v122/bg122153.pdf |title=Feuding Gentry and an Affray on College Green, Bristol, in 1579 |publisher=Bristol and Gloucestershire Archaeological Society |accessdate=16 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029201338/http://www2.glos.ac.uk/bgas/tbgas/v122/bg122153.pdf |archivedate=29 October 2013 }}</ref>。他在1568年建造了大宅。而红屋最初是用作杨府招待客人的客房以及花园和果园。<ref name=" Black Lives ">{{cite book | year = 2008 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=B2F-SVZD08kC&q=red+lodge+john+young&pg=PA208 | title = Black Lives in the English Archives, 1500–1677| publisher = Ashgate Publishing |isbn = 9780754656951| accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref>

约翰·杨爵士于1589年去世，他的遗孀琼夫人(1533–1603)于1590年完成红屋。琼夫人来自一个古老的萨默塞特和德文家族，是[[牛津大学沃德姆学院|牛津大学沃德姆学院]]创始人尼古拉斯·沃德姆的妹妹。1574年[[伊丽莎白一世|伊丽莎白一世]]访问布里斯托尔时，就住在杨府，并授予他骑士勋章，家族纹章刻在红屋大橡树厅的门廊入口上方。琼夫人精美的雕像位于附近的[[布里斯托尔座堂|布里斯托尔座堂]]的西门。

他们的儿子罗伯特·杨<ref name=" Feuding Gentry " />继承了遗产。他很快耗尽了遗产，被迫将红屋传给同母异父的兄弟尼古拉斯·斯特朗威，以避免扣押。<ref name=" A Chronological Outline of the History of Bristol ">{{cite book | year = 1824 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=_9JCAAAAYAAJ&q=red+lodge+nicholas+strangeways&pg=PA161 | title = A Chronological Outline of the History of Bristol and the Stranger's Guide Through its Streets and Neighbourhood| publisher = John Evans | accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref> 到1595 年，建筑出租给各种租户，独立于大宅。<ref name=" Pastscape ">{{PastScape | year = 2007 | mnumber = 1008234 | mname= Red Lodge Museum| accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref> 罗伯特最终把大宅出售给阿什顿庄园的休·斯米斯爵士。<ref name=" ONDB Smyth ">{{cite web | year = 2013 | url = http://www.oxforddnb.com/templates/article.jsp?articleid=71874&back= | title = Oxford DNB Smyth Family| publisher = Oxford DNB | accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref>

1730年代，约翰和玛丽·亨利买下了红屋，开始在北侧进行大型扩建工程<ref name=" Time Travel Britain ">{{cite web | year = 2006 | url = http://www.timetravel-britain.com/articles/houses/lodge.shtml | title = Time Travel Britain: Bristol's Red Lodge and it's Elizabethan Knot Garden | publisher = Yvonne Cuthbertson | accessdate = 16 September 2013 | archive-date = 2013-08-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130829205106/http://www.timetravel-britain.com/articles/houses/lodge.shtml | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name=" Pevsner Bristol ">{{cite book | year = 2004 | url = https://archive.org/details/bristol0000foyl | url-access = registration | page = [https://archive.org/details/bristol0000foyl/page/250 250] | quote = red lodge bristol parlour ceiling. | title = Bristol Pevsner Guide (Andrew Foyle)| publisher = Yale | accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref>。完工之前，约翰·亨利去世，玛丽·亨利由于没有孩子，无法继承。约翰的遗嘱写道，玛丽有权每年在红屋住一个月。这意味着建筑物不能长期出租或出售给新业主<ref>{{cite web|title=1747 February 11 Copy of Will of John Day of Bristol, esq., – inter alia, the Red...|url=http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/rd/81744280-cac7-49ea-976c-ebb159a84963|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=6 December 2015|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304043754/http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/rd/81744280-cac7-49ea-976c-ebb159a84963|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

亨利去世后，红屋出租给在布里斯托尔皇家医院行医的房客，包括写《人类物理史研究》的詹姆斯·考尔斯·普里查德，以及弗朗西斯·谢恩·鲍尔斯和理查德·史密斯，他们利用大橡树室作为解剖剧院。<ref name=" Bristol's Anatomy History ">{{cite web | year = 2003 | url = http://d-mis-web.ana.bris.ac.uk/personal/mark/Anatomy_teaching_in_bristol.htm | title = University of Bristol D-mis homepage | publisher = University of Bristol | accessdate = 16 September 2013| archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130917205750/http://d-mis-web.ana.bris.ac.uk/personal/mark/Anatomy_teaching_in_bristol.htm | archivedate = 17 September 2013}}</ref>

1854年，拜伦夫人用[[拜伦勋爵|拜伦勋爵]]的遗赠买下了这座建筑，并捐赠给热心的改革者玛丽·卡彭特，在此开办女子改革学校。<ref name=" Victorian Childhood ">{{cite book | year = 1987 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=xptgUkJxJQsC&q=red+lodge+bristol+1854+Mary+Carpenter&pg=PA287 | title = Victorian Childhood: Themes and Variations| publisher = University of New York |isbn = 9780887065446| accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=" Mary Carpenter and the Children of the Streets " />。一直开办到1917年。卡彭特利用她[[教育长|教育长]]的地位，周游世界，研究穷人儿童的困境。<ref name=" Mary Carpenter and the Children of the Streets ">{{cite book | year = 1976 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=wkVHAAAAMAAJ&q=red+lodge+bristol+1854+Mary+Carpenter | title = Mary Carpenter and the Children of the Streets| publisher = Heinemann Educational | accessdate = 16 September 2013}}</ref> 

